		<td><b>VRC7 question</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Here's a question:
<br />
<br />I'm daydreaming about a homebrew project which would have VRC7 audio. Easy enough in an emulator, but I'd like to be able to make some game cartridges out of it, and there's no way I'd sacrifice a <em>Lagrange Point</em> cartridge for the silly little game I have in mind. So the other option is to sacrifice a Japanese <em>Tiny Toon Adventures 2</em> cartridge, a significantly less colossal loss. This wouldn't have any negative effects on the game, which would do just fine with CHR-ROM, doesn't need SRAM, and would definitely fit in 128KB PRG-ROM and 128KB CHR-ROM. My only question is this: TTA2 (J) doesn't use the VRC7 audio, but the audio generator's still present in the cartridge, right? Or is the sound expansion a separate chip which is present in <em>Lagrange Point</em> but not <em>TTA2</em>?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


