		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have both carts; Tiny Toons 2 is a regular size Konami cart, Lagrange is an oversized cart. I bet TT2 doesn't have at least the audio circuit if not the external IC (if that's the case); that or it's an entirely different ASIC only operationally similar to the VRC7. Also, I paid about twice as much for Tiny Toons 2 ($16) as I did for Lagrange ($9) in a Tokyo used gameshop, I think Japanese eBay shops will charge accordingly to what they buy the carts for. 
<br />
<br />Also remember that Konami carts snap together only so they won't be the cleanest to open (or else I'd check for you) :)

		

