	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Something to note:<div class="quotetitle"><a href="http://nesdevwiki.ath.cx/index.php/Konami_VRC7#Registers" class="postlink">NESdevWiki:Konami VRC7#Registers</a> wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">One variant of the VRC7 uses A4 for registers ($x010), another uses A3 ($x008). Additionally, A5 is used on the first mentioned variant only for sound registers ($x030)</div>
<br />Clarification: My point is that Lagrange Point and TTA2j must at least have different wirings (and possibly different revisions of the VRC7 chip, although I'm not sure whether that matters).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
